Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Roma Tomato{2} into ½-inch cubes. Add half the tomatoes to a #medium pan{} and place over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the @Orzo Pasta{6} from package (use the rest as you like). Cook, stirring, for about ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour @water{1%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{} into pan. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to medium. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. (TIP: If mixture seems dry, add more water, ¼ cup at a time, to loosen.) Remove pan from heat and stir in @Garlic Herb Butter{2}, two thirds of the @Baby Spinach{5}, and half the @Parmesan Cheese{¼}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @Chicken Cutlets{20} dry with a #paper towel{}; set aside half. Season other half with salt, pepper, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1}. Add seasoned chicken to pan and cook until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside. Mix @Panko Breadcrumbs{½}, remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, and a big pinch of salt on a #plate{}.

  Season remaining chicken with salt and pepper. Brush with 2 TBSP @Sour Cream{6} (1 packet). Dip into panko mixture one piece at a time, coating all over and pressing to adhere. Transfer to another plate. Heat a ¼-inch layer of oil in another large pan over high heat (we used nonstick). Add breaded chicken and cook until crisp and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side, lowering heat if it browns too quickly. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with salt.

Halve @Lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, toss half the remaining spinach with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2} and a squeeze of lemon. Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Divide breaded chicken and orzotto between plates. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Scatter dressed spinach over chicken and serve.

After dinner, cut seasoned chicken and @Fresh Mozzarella{4} into small pieces (about ½ inch). Toss both in a #medium bowl{} with remaining tomatoes, a squeeze or two of lemon, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Keep refrigerated overnight. In the morning, toss remaining spinach into chicken mixture. Split @Whole Wheat Pitas{2}, then fill each with chicken mixture and pack. Enjoy cold or at room temperature.

> Pack the pitas separately and fill just before eating for best results.